4
00:00:41,403 --> 00:00:44,993
<font color="#ffff00">第五季 第三集</font>
<font color="#ffff00">S5E03</font>

5
00:01:06,052 --> 00:01:09,150
这是"王子"的马厩
And this is where the Prince is stabled.

6
00:01:10,065 --> 00:01:12,042
啊 Robert爵士
Oh, Sir Robert.

7
00:01:12,158 --> 00:01:14,036
很抱歉打扰你
Sorry to disturb you.

8
00:01:14,146 --> 00:01:16,619
这是Joe Barnes
This is Joe Barnes.

9
00:01:16,728 --> 00:01:17,570
Josiah的儿子
Josiah's boy.

10
00:01:17,608 --> 00:01:18,716
我知道他是谁 Mason
I know who he is, Mason.

11
00:01:18,754 --> 00:01:19,934
他在这儿干什么?
What's he doing here?

12
00:01:20,391 --> 00:01:23,071
他对赛马很感兴趣
He's keen to race horses.

13
00:01:23,183 --> 00:01:24,708
我会骑马 Robert爵士
I can ride, Sir Robert.

14
00:01:24,745 --> 00:01:26,425
我想要做骑师
I'd love to be a jockey.

15
00:01:26,533 --> 00:01:27,149
是吗?
Would you?

16
00:01:27,186 --> 00:01:28,773
超过任何愿望
More than anything in the world.

17
00:01:28,810 --> 00:01:31,624
嗯 很好 非常好
Well, that's good, very good.

18
00:01:31,731 --> 00:01:34,371
但这跟我有什么关系?
But what has it got to do with me?

19
00:01:34,488 --> 00:01:35,801
我想我可以为你工作
Well, I thought I could work for you.

20
00:01:35,838 --> 00:01:39,687
我已经有足够的骑师了
I have all the jockeys I need.

21
00:01:40,210 --> 00:01:42,196
请给我一次机会吧 先生
Please give me a chance, sir.

22
00:01:42,303 --> 00:01:43,896
我可以清理马厩的垃圾
I'll muck out the stables,

23
00:01:44,013 --> 00:01:45,475
清扫马场
clean the yard,

24
00:01:45,584 --> 00:01:47,462
随您吩咐
anything you want.

25
00:01:47,573 --> 00:01:49,165
我考虑一下
I'll think about it.

26
00:01:49,283 --> 00:01:51,400
谢谢您 Robert爵士
Thank you, Sir Robert.

27
00:01:51,515 --> 00:01:53,666
先生 您最好赶紧回屋一趟
Sir, at the house, you better come quick.

28
00:01:53,784 --> 00:01:54,543
怎么了?
Why?

29
00:01:54,580 --> 00:01:56,917
有麻烦了 先生
There's trouble, sir.

30
00:02:01,670 --> 00:02:04,732
我告诉过你Beatrice夫人不舒服
I told you Lady Beatrice is unwell

31
00:02:04,844 --> 00:02:06,508
不想被打扰
and does not wish to be disturbed.

32
00:02:06,545 --> 00:02:09,341
我想我会成为她的特例
I think she'll make an exception in my case.

33
00:02:09,451 --> 00:02:11,959
很抱歉 先生
I'm sorry, sir.

34
00:02:12,067 --> 00:02:15,587
我接到严格的指示
I have strict instructions.

35
00:02:15,696 --> 00:02:18,657
你是让我跟Beatrice夫人谈谈
Are you going to let me speak to Lady Beatrice

36
00:02:18,767 --> 00:02:21,097
还是逼我使用暴力?
or will I have to use force?

37
00:02:23,302 --> 00:02:26,085
你得先过我这关 Brewer
You'll answer to me first, Brewer.

38
00:02:26,199 --> 00:02:28,077
这位先生坚持
This gentleman is most insistent

39
00:02:28,187 --> 00:02:30,715
要与夫人谈话 先生
upon speaking to her ladyship, sir.

40
00:02:35,584 --> 00:02:36,655
我警告过你永远不要到这儿来
I warned you never to come here.

41
00:02:36,692 --> 00:02:39,390
我们的事可以在你的办公室谈 不是这里
Our business can be discussed at your office, not here.

42
00:02:39,428 --> 00:02:42,339
我在很多场合试图解决这个问题
I've tried to settle this matter on many occasions.

43
00:02:42,377 --> 00:02:44,094
你该知道的 Robert爵士
As you well know, Sir Robert.

44
00:02:44,130 --> 00:02:47,444
想不到在New Market发生那事之后 你居然还有胆子来
You've got a nerve coming here after New Market.

45
00:02:47,552 --> 00:02:50,656
这次我有把握
I'm leaving nothing to chance this time.

46
00:02:50,762 --> 00:02:53,171
或许Beatrice夫人更乐于
Perhaps Lady Beatrice will be more prepared

47
00:02:53,210 --> 00:02:54,286
听听理由
to listen to reason.

48
00:02:54,323 --> 00:02:55,834
这是你我之间的恩怨 Brewer
Your grievance is with me, Brewer,

49
00:02:55,871 --> 00:02:56,969
与他人无关
and with no one else.

50
00:02:57,007 --> 00:03:00,583
这当然与Beatrice夫人有关系
It would certainly be of concern to Lady Beatrice.

51
00:03:03,245 --> 00:03:06,417
Robert 这些人是谁?
Robert, who are these people?

52
00:03:06,532 --> 00:03:08,268
他们要干什么?
And what do they want?

53
00:03:08,383 --> 00:03:09,811
我来告诉你我要干什么 Beatrice夫人
I'll tell you what I want, Lady Beatrice.

54
00:03:09,848 --> 00:03:10,542
请他出去
Get him out of here.

55
00:03:10,579 --> 00:03:12,921
我要要回自己的东西!
I want what's rightfully mine.

56
00:03:13,418 --> 00:03:14,577
出去
Get out.

57
00:03:14,615 --> 00:03:18,666
滚! 趁你两条腿还能走
Go while you can still walk.

58
00:03:18,703 --> 00:03:21,235
我会再来的 Beatrice夫人
I'll be back, Lady Beatrice.

59
00:03:21,273 --> 00:03:22,709
再会
Good day to you.

60
00:03:33,134 --> 00:03:35,096
很抱歉让你烦心 亲爱的
I'm sorry you've been upset, my dear.

61
00:03:35,134 --> 00:03:37,099
他是什么意思 Robert?
What did he mean, Robert,

62
00:03:37,136 --> 00:03:39,217
什么是本应属于他的?
what's rightfully his?

63
00:03:39,254 --> 00:03:41,275
没什么可担心的
Nothing for you to worry about.

64
00:03:41,312 --> 00:03:44,190
但我的确很担心 Robert
But I do worry, Robert.

65
00:03:44,228 --> 00:03:46,432
我太了解你了
I know you too well.

66
00:03:58,252 --> 00:04:00,909
他不会再来烦我们了
He won't bother us again.

67
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:15,089
如果他真的再来我们该怎么办 先生?
What should we do if he does come back, sir?

68
00:04:15,126 --> 00:04:17,598
如果他再来
If he does come back,

69
00:04:17,636 --> 00:04:20,329
我会亲自处理
I'll deal with him myself.

70
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:49,587
<font color="#ffff00">肖斯科姆别墅</font>
<font color="#ffff00">Shoscombe Old Place</font>

71
00:05:12,633 --> 00:05:15,082
华生 你懂赛马吗?
Watson, do you know a bit of racing?

72
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:17,268
照理说应该懂一点
I ought to.

73
00:05:17,305 --> 00:05:19,745
我的负伤抚恤金有一半都花在了这上面
I paid for it with about half my wound pension.

74
00:05:19,783 --> 00:05:23,497
那我要把你当作我的"赛马指南"了
Then I'll give you my handy guide to the turf.

75
00:05:23,535 --> 00:05:24,385
你的什么?
Your what?

76
00:05:24,422 --> 00:05:27,581
你记得Robert Norberton这个名字吗?
Does the name Sir Robert Norberton recall anything?

77
00:05:27,619 --> 00:05:29,313
小心
Careful.

78
00:05:30,387 --> 00:05:33,131
他的马驹参加了冠军锦标赛
He's got a horse running in the Champion Stakes.

79
00:05:33,144 --> 00:05:35,333
他住在Shoscombe庄园
He lives at Shoscombe Hall.

80
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:37,947
他的马厩在当地 被称为Shoscombe别墅
His stables are known locally as Shoscombe Old Place.

81
00:05:37,985 --> 00:05:39,643
但你并不认识他本人?
But you don't know the man himself?

82
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,005
我从没见过他 如果你是这个意思
I never met him if that's what you mean.

83
00:05:42,713 --> 00:05:45,852
他是出了名的危险人物
He has a reputation of being rather a dangerous man.

84
00:05:45,891 --> 00:05:47,081
怎么个危险法?
How dangerous?

85
00:05:47,117 --> 00:05:48,812
我记得数月前有一次
I remember an instance some months ago

86
00:05:48,850 --> 00:05:51,090
他在New Market Heath用马鞭抽了一个人
when he horsewhipped a man on New Market Heath.

87
00:05:51,127 --> 00:05:54,185
是Samuel Brewer Carson街的一位放债人
Samuel Brewer, the Carson Street moneylender.

88
00:05:54,223 --> 00:05:56,105
为什么会发生这样的攻击事件?
What was the reason for this assault?

89
00:05:56,144 --> 00:05:59,285
我猜是Robert爵士忌恨债主
Well, I imagine that Sir Robert had a grudge against moneylenders.

90
00:05:59,322 --> 00:06:00,812
也就是说他负债累累
Or is heavily in their debt.

91
00:06:00,850 --> 00:06:02,809
据说 他目前是日陷窘境
Well, by all accounts, he's so far down Queer Street,

92
00:06:02,846 --> 00:06:04,401
可能再也不能恢复往日风光
he may never find his way back again.

93
00:06:04,438 --> 00:06:07,489
我收到了John Mason的信
I received a letter from John Mason,

94
00:06:07,527 --> 00:06:09,480
他是Shoscombe的首席训练师
the head trainer at Shoscombe.

95
00:06:09,517 --> 00:06:11,277
信是一小时前寄到的
It arrived an hour ago.

96
00:06:12,540 --> 00:06:14,119
亲爱的福尔摩斯先生
Dear Mr. Holmes,

97
00:06:14,156 --> 00:06:15,504
您一定已经得知
you will no doubt have read

98
00:06:15,543 --> 00:06:19,889
Samuel Brewer在几天前失踪的消息
of the disappearance a number of days ago of Samuel Brewer.

99
00:06:19,926 --> 00:06:22,469
为了我的雇主Robert Norberton爵士的利益
In the interests of my employer, Sir Robert Norberton,

100
00:06:22,506 --> 00:06:24,552
我想拜访您
I should like to visit you

101
00:06:24,590 --> 00:06:26,856
来商谈一件十万火急的事件
to discuss a matter of the utmost urgency.

102
00:06:26,894 --> 00:06:28,436
他不是约了时间嘛
He suggests a convenient time?

103
00:06:28,473 --> 00:06:31,124
已经晚了几分钟
And already is several minutes late.

104
00:06:31,162 --> 00:06:33,494
Samuel Brewer失踪了
Samuel Brewer's disappeared.

105
00:06:33,531 --> 00:06:35,400
报纸已经大肆报道
The newspapers make a lot of it,

106
00:06:35,438 --> 00:06:36,862
但我们还是先来说说Shoscombe吧
but let's hear more about Shoscombe.

107
00:06:36,899 --> 00:06:38,922
Shoscombe犬
Well, the Shoscombe spaniels,

108
00:06:38,961 --> 00:06:41,691
是Shoscombe别墅女主人的骄傲
special pride of the lady of Shoscombe Place.

109
00:06:41,729 --> 00:06:43,729
她是Robert Norberton的妻子？
The wife of Sir Robert Norberton I presume.

110
00:06:43,766 --> 00:06:45,123
不 不 他没结过婚
No, no, He never married.

111
00:06:45,161 --> 00:06:47,185
他和他的姐姐 一位遗孀
He lives with his widowed sister,

112
00:06:47,222 --> 00:06:49,696
Beatrice Folder夫人住在一起
Lady Beatrice Folder.

113
00:06:49,734 --> 00:06:51,041
你是说 她寄住在他那里？
You mean she lives with him?

114
00:06:51,078 --> 00:06:55,368
不 不 房子属于她的前夫 James爵士
No, no, the place belonged to her late husband, Sir James.

115
00:06:55,827 --> 00:06:57,879
Shoscombe会出什么事呢?
What should be amiss at Shoscombe?

116
00:06:57,917 --> 00:06:59,694
到底是怎么回事呢?
What indeed?

117
00:07:00,208 --> 00:07:02,168
希望门外那位能够告诉我们
And here I expect is the man who can tell us.

118
00:07:02,206 --> 00:07:03,812
请进
Yes?

119
00:07:05,147 --> 00:07:07,291
我的蛋煮老了
My eggs were hard boiled.

120
00:07:07,328 --> 00:07:09,914
有一位Mason先生想要见您 先生
There's a Mr. Mason to see you, sir.

121
00:07:09,953 --> 00:07:11,450
谢谢 Hudson女士 请他进来
Thank you, Mrs. Hudson, show him in.

122
00:07:11,487 --> 00:07:14,641
是 先生
Sir.

123
00:07:14,679 --> 00:07:16,669
这边请
If you'll come this way.

124
00:07:19,292 --> 00:07:22,340
-福尔摩斯先生 您收到我的信了吗? -是的
-You got my note, Mr. Holmes? -Yes.

125
00:07:22,818 --> 00:07:24,357
但里面什么都没说
But it explained nothing.

126
00:07:24,937 --> 00:07:26,399
要把细节都付诸文字
It was too delicate a thing

127
00:07:26,436 --> 00:07:28,815
实在太难下手了
for me to put the details on paper.

128
00:07:29,278 --> 00:07:31,464
事情太复杂了
It was too complicated.

129
00:07:31,502 --> 00:07:34,366
你可以信任我的朋友兼同事  华生医生的谨言慎行
You may rely on the discretion of my friend and colleague, Dr. Watson.

130
00:07:34,403 --> 00:07:37,321
-请坐 -谢谢
Please sit down. Thank you.

131
00:07:45,144 --> 00:07:47,346
福尔摩斯先生
Mr. Holmes,

132
00:07:47,660 --> 00:07:50,311
我想Robert Norberton爵士是疯了
I think Sir Robert Norberton has gone mad.

133
00:07:50,349 --> 00:07:53,674
拜托 这里是Baker街 不是Harley街 (伦敦著名的医疗街)
Please, this is Baker Street not Harley Street.

134
00:07:53,712 --> 00:07:54,801
你为什么这么说?
Why do you say so?

135
00:07:54,838 --> 00:07:58,551
我想是"Shoscombe王子"和冠军锦标赛
I believe Shoscombe Prince and the Champion Stakes

136
00:07:58,589 --> 00:08:00,786
把他弄成这样的
have turned his brain.

137
00:08:00,823 --> 00:08:05,558
-"Shoscombe王子"? - (马驹)
Shoscombe Prince?

138
00:08:05,596 --> 00:08:08,189
华生 你真是无价之宝  一匹吗?
Watson, you're invaluable. A horse?

139
00:08:08,226 --> 00:08:09,998
全英格兰最好的马 先生
The finest in England, sir.

140
00:08:10,036 --> 00:08:14,353
事实上 Robert爵士必须赢得比赛
The truth is Sir Robert has got to win this race.

141
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:17,625
他已经无路可走 这是最后的机会了
He's up to his neck, and it's his last chance.

142
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:20,662
他把所有能够筹集的财产都押在了这匹马上
He's wagered everything he could raise or borrow on the horse,

143
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,139
他把所有欠款
and he's holding off his creditors

144
00:08:22,176 --> 00:08:24,022
都拖延到大赛之后归还
till after the big race.

145
00:08:24,059 --> 00:08:27,477
如果"王子"输掉了比赛 他就完蛋了
Oh, if the Prince fails him, he's done for.

146
00:08:27,515 --> 00:08:30,652
你是猜测Robert爵士的债务
And you're assuming there's a connection between Sir Robert's debts

147
00:08:30,690 --> 00:08:33,584
与Samuel Brewer的失踪之间有关联
and the disappearance of Samuel Brewer.

148
00:08:33,622 --> 00:08:36,238
他是Robert爵士的主要债权人
He's Sir Robert's principal creditor,

149
00:08:36,276 --> 00:08:37,849
而且我得指出
and I don't mind admitting

150
00:08:37,885 --> 00:08:40,308
他们之间没有任何好感
there's no love lost between them.

151
00:08:40,346 --> 00:08:42,368
在New Market的事情发生之后
Well, after what happened at New Market

152
00:08:42,405 --> 00:08:43,964
我一点也不惊讶
I'm not surprised.

153
00:08:44,002 --> 00:08:45,926
但那仅仅是开始
But that was just the start.

154
00:08:45,963 --> 00:08:48,004
Brewer上周在庄园露面
Brewer showed his face at the hall last week,

155
00:08:48,042 --> 00:08:50,766
Robert爵士像疯了一样朝他发飙
and Sir Robert flew at him like a man possessed.

156
00:08:50,803 --> 00:08:52,341
说如果他再出现
Said he'd deal with him

157
00:08:52,379 --> 00:08:53,919
他会亲自收拾他
if he ever showed his face there again.

158
00:08:53,957 --> 00:08:56,454
我想他再也没回来
I presume he has not returned.

159
00:08:56,491 --> 00:08:58,548
我不知道 先生
I don't know, sir.

160
00:08:58,586 --> 00:09:00,301
不确定
Not for sure.

161
00:09:00,339 --> 00:09:01,678
了解
I see.

162
00:09:01,714 --> 00:09:04,780
如果财产危机真的发生
In the event of financial catastrophe,

163
00:09:04,819 --> 00:09:07,690
Robert爵士有权主张他姐姐的地产吗?
would Sir Robert have any claim on his sister's estate?

164
00:09:07,728 --> 00:09:10,600
据我所知不行
None at all as far as I know.

165
00:09:10,638 --> 00:09:12,482
她只有非世袭的财产所有权
She only has a life interest in it.

166
00:09:12,483 --> 00:09:16,316
在她死后 地产将归她丈夫的兄弟所有
It reverts to her husband's  brother after her death.

167
00:09:16,316 --> 00:09:17,251
同时
In the meantime,

168
00:09:17,288 --> 00:09:20,021
她能以夫人的身份收取年租
her ladyship draws the rents every year.

169
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:22,216
而钱都被她弟弟花掉了?
And her brother spends them?

170
00:09:22,254 --> 00:09:24,170
差不多
That's about the size of it.

171
00:09:24,206 --> 00:09:27,790
他的生活一定很坎坷
He must lead a most uneasy life?

172
00:09:27,828 --> 00:09:30,845
或许吧 但他们一直是挚友
Well, maybe so, but they've  always been the best of friends.

173
00:09:30,883 --> 00:09:32,981
他们志同道合
They have the same tastes.

174
00:09:33,020 --> 00:09:37,068
她跟他一样热爱赛马
She loves the horses as much as he does.

175
00:09:37,068 --> 00:09:41,377
至少曾经是
Or at least she did.

176
00:09:42,739 --> 00:09:44,021
以前每天12点
Every day at about 12:00

177
00:09:44,058 --> 00:09:46,324
她都要驱车去马厩看马
she'd ride down to the stables to see them.

178
00:09:46,362 --> 00:09:48,666
尤其是
And above all,

179
00:09:48,704 --> 00:09:51,417
她十分喜爱"王子"
she loved the Prince.

180
00:09:54,821 --> 00:09:56,430
早上好 Beatrice
Good morning, Beatrice.

181
00:10:00,028 --> 00:10:01,595
我等不及想看看当这个讨喜的小家伙
I can't wait to see their faces

182
00:10:01,633 --> 00:10:04,100
第一个冲过终点柱的时候 他们会是什么表情
when this delightful creature is first past the post.

183
00:10:04,137 --> 00:10:05,092
你怎么说 Mason?
What say you, Mason?

184
00:10:05,129 --> 00:10:07,288
其它马不会有胜算 先生
The others won't stand a chance, sir.

185
00:10:07,326 --> 00:10:08,871
赢它们三个身长 你说呢?
A three-length win, wouldn't you say?

186
00:10:08,908 --> 00:10:11,194
三个半身长 至少
Three and a half, at least.

187
00:10:12,584 --> 00:10:15,632
只是不要期望太高 Robert
Just beware of raising your hopes too high, Robert.

188
00:10:15,670 --> 00:10:17,550
你不是唯一一个想让自己的赛马
You're not the only one who'd like to see

189
00:10:17,587 --> 00:10:20,253
在冠军锦标赛上夺冠的人
his horse win the Champion Stakes.

190
00:10:20,291 --> 00:10:24,070
但我是唯一一个拥有 "Shoscombe王子"的人
I'm the only one with a horse like Shoscombe Prince.

191
00:10:24,108 --> 00:10:25,609
它的状态怎么这么好
Why he's on such good form,

192
00:10:25,645 --> 00:10:27,713
你甚至可以亲自骑着它去夺冠 亲爱的
you could ride him to victory yourself, my dear.

193
00:10:27,751 --> 00:10:29,723
我想不行了 Robert
I think not, Robert.

194
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:33,047
我们骑马的日子已经结束了
Our riding days are over.

195
00:10:48,991 --> 00:10:51,690
你该休息的 亲爱的
You should be resting, my dear.

196
00:10:52,355 --> 00:10:53,468
不 我很好 Robert
No, I'm fine, Robert.

197
00:10:53,505 --> 00:10:54,868
真的 我很好
Really, I'm fine.

198
00:10:54,905 --> 00:10:56,578
你知道医生的叮嘱
You know what the doctor said.

199
00:10:56,616 --> 00:11:00,556
你比他还要大惊小怪
You fuss even more than he does.

200
00:11:02,592 --> 00:11:05,391
Jasper 真乖
Jasper, good dog.

201
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:09,358
Carrie 你今天怎么样?
And how's Carrie today?

202
00:11:09,931 --> 00:11:14,077
很好 谢谢 Robert爵士
Oh, very well, thank you, Sir Robert.

203
00:11:20,998 --> 00:11:22,025
而在过去一周
But for the past week,

204
00:11:22,062 --> 00:11:23,926
她的马车依然驶过马厩
her ladyship has driven past the stables

205
00:11:23,963 --> 00:11:26,739
却再也没有来打过招呼
with never so much  as a good morning.

206
00:11:27,762 --> 00:11:31,107
你认为他们之间有了争执吗?
Do you think there's been some sort of quarrel?

207
00:11:31,145 --> 00:11:34,625
是彼此怀恨 来势汹汹  剑拔弩张的一次争吵
And a bitter, savage, spiteful quarrel at that.

208
00:11:34,664 --> 00:11:36,495
现在 他都不会接近她
Now, he never goes near her.

209
00:11:36,532 --> 00:11:38,430
她几乎都不离开房间
She hardly leaves her room

210
00:11:38,468 --> 00:11:40,622
除了每天乘车出行
except to take her daily drive.

211
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:43,892
我想你亲眼目睹了这场争论的发生
And I assume that you have witnessed such a disagreement?

212
00:11:43,931 --> 00:11:46,871
不 没有
Well, no, not exactly.

213
00:11:46,909 --> 00:11:51,522
但否则为什么他要把她的宠物狗 送走呢 福尔摩斯先生?
But why else would he give away her pet spaniel, Mr. Holmes?

214
00:11:51,559 --> 00:11:55,420
她喜欢那只狗 视如己出
She loved that dog as if it were her child.

215
00:11:55,457 --> 00:11:59,165
你能给出任何理由为什么Robert爵士
Can you think of any reason why Sir Robert

216
00:11:59,203 --> 00:12:02,324
要以这种方式令他的姐姐难过吗?
would wish to upset his sister in this fashion?

217
00:12:02,362 --> 00:12:03,990
想不通
None at all.

218
00:12:04,027 --> 00:12:07,033
这样对待一位心脏脆弱的女士实在太残忍了
It's a cruel way to treat a woman with a weak heart.

219
00:12:07,070 --> 00:12:09,311
简直差劲透了
It's damn rotten.

220
00:12:10,748 --> 00:12:16,188
我得说我并不认为他犯了什么罪
I must say he does not appear to be  committing any crime that I recognize.

221
00:12:18,165 --> 00:12:22,101
那为什么Robert爵士要在夜里离开宅子?
So why did Sir Robert leave the house at the dead of night,

222
00:12:22,138 --> 00:12:24,128
他去见的人是谁呢?
and who was the man he met?

223
00:12:24,165 --> 00:12:25,975
说下去
Go on.

224
00:12:27,567 --> 00:12:29,829
是管家Stephens看到他出了门
Well, it was Stephens, the butler, who saw him leave,

225
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:31,888
然后告诉了我
and he told me about it.

226
00:12:32,418 --> 00:12:36,637
所以第二天夜里我们跟踪了他
So the next night we followed him.

227
00:13:09,559 --> 00:13:11,848
那是谁
Who was it?

228
00:13:12,487 --> 00:13:18,149
-Samuel Brewer? -当时太黑了 看不清他的脸
-Samuel Brewer? -It's too dark to see his face.

229
00:13:18,186 --> 00:13:20,538
Robert爵士在什么时候送走了他姐姐的狗?
When did Sir Robert give away his sister's dog?

230
00:13:20,575 --> 00:13:23,014
一周前的今天
A week ago today.

231
00:13:23,053 --> 00:13:26,679
Jasper在磨坊里鬼哭狼嚎
Jasper was howling like a banshee at the mill house,

232
00:13:26,717 --> 00:13:30,720
但身为主人也不该就这么送人呀
but that was no good reason for the master to do what he did.

233
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:42,291
Robert爵士
Sir Robert.

234
00:13:42,738 --> 00:13:44,832
我要它离开这里
I want it offthis estate.

235
00:13:44,870 --> 00:13:46,787
我不在乎你怎么处置它
I don't care what you do with it

236
00:13:46,823 --> 00:13:49,502
只要别再让我看到它
just as long as I never have to see it again.

237
00:13:51,670 --> 00:13:52,678
好的 先生
Yes, sir.

238
00:13:53,918 --> 00:13:55,969
我把狗给了Sandy Bain
I gave the dog to Sandy Bain,

239
00:13:56,007 --> 00:13:57,797
一位骑师
the jockey.

240
00:13:57,834 --> 00:14:00,493
好了 Jasper
Right then, Jasper.

241
00:14:00,531 --> 00:14:03,997
我们去喝点东西吧
Let's you and I go for a drink, hey.

242
00:14:04,035 --> 00:14:04,727
走吧
Come on.

243
00:14:04,764 --> 00:14:07,004
第二天早上 他把狗给了Josiah Barnes
Next morning, he took it to Josiah Barnes,

244
00:14:07,042 --> 00:14:09,894
Crendall那儿的Green Dragon旅馆的老板
the landlord at the Green Dragon in Crendall.

245
00:14:11,486 --> 00:14:13,943
Beatrice夫人有贴身伴侣吗?
Does Lady Beatrice have a companion?

246
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:15,587
有个女仆 福尔摩斯先生
Her maid, Mr. Holmes.

247
00:14:15,625 --> 00:14:16,505
只有一个?
Just the one?

248
00:14:16,542 --> 00:14:17,659
Carrie Evans
Carrie Evans.

249
00:14:17,696 --> 00:14:20,120
但她已经跟随夫人五年了
But she's been with her this five years.

250
00:14:20,158 --> 00:14:22,449
那她很忠心了?
And is no doubt devoted?

251
00:14:22,487 --> 00:14:25,636
她的确很忠心 不过我不能说是对谁
She is devoted enough, and I won't say to whom.

252
00:14:25,673 --> 00:14:28,221
哦?
Uh-huh.

253
00:14:28,258 --> 00:14:31,217
我不能搬弄是非
I can't tell tales out of school.

254
00:14:32,088 --> 00:14:36,018
Robert爵士挺会讨女人欢心的吧?
Sir Robert is something of a lady's man, hey?

255
00:14:36,055 --> 00:14:37,446
你不觉得姐弟间的不睦
Do you not think the quarrel

256
00:14:37,483 --> 00:14:39,506
可能是由此产生的吗?
between brother and sister may lie there?

257
00:14:39,544 --> 00:14:42,582
哦 这个流言早已是人尽皆知了
Oh, that scandal has been  pretty clear for a long time.

258
00:14:42,620 --> 00:14:44,396
但Beatrice夫人或许之前没有发现
But Lady Beatrice may not have seen it before.

259
00:14:44,433 --> 00:14:47,617
让我们假设她突然知晓了
Let us suppose that she suddenly found it out,

260
00:14:47,655 --> 00:14:50,522
于是要辞退这个讨她厌的女仆
and she wants to be rid of the hated maid.

261
00:14:50,524 --> 00:14:52,043
但他不同意
He will not permit it.

262
00:14:52,044 --> 00:14:54,185
于是她拒绝跟他说话
She refuses to speak to him.

263
00:14:54,223 --> 00:14:55,923
而Robert爵士一怒之下
And Sir Robert in his anger

264
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,406
送走了她的爱犬
gives away her dog.

265
00:14:57,444 --> 00:15:00,629
不止这些 福尔摩斯先生
There's more to it than that, Mr. Holmes.

266
00:15:00,667 --> 00:15:03,187
Mason先生
Mr. Mason,

267
00:15:03,187 --> 00:15:05,457
你比我们有优势
you have the advantage of us.

268
00:15:07,458 --> 00:15:09,217
可能还有些你
Perhaps there is something

269
00:15:09,255 --> 00:15:12,871
没有告诉我们的事
that you have not told us.

270
00:15:16,201 --> 00:15:20,117
地下室里有个中央暖气锅炉
There's a central heating furnace in the cellar.

271
00:15:30,181 --> 00:15:31,881
已经许久未用了
It's been off for some time,

272
00:15:31,919 --> 00:15:34,972
但Robert爵士抱怨天冷
but Sir Robert complained of cold.

273
00:15:35,010 --> 00:15:36,941
又把它烧了起来
And had it on again.

274
00:15:36,978 --> 00:15:37,799
Harvey负责烧锅炉
Harvey runs it.

275
00:15:37,837 --> 00:15:40,312
他是我的一个伙计
He's one of my lads.

276
00:15:41,802 --> 00:15:45,169
他感到不妙 福尔摩斯先生
He didn't like the look of it, Mr. Holmes.

277
00:15:46,871 --> 00:15:49,402
昨晚把这个交个了我
And he brought it to me last night.

278
00:15:49,741 --> 00:15:52,592
Harvey多久烧一次炉子?
How often does Harvey attend the furnace?

279
00:15:52,631 --> 00:15:54,249
他每晚把炉子烧起来
He makes it up every evening,

280
00:15:54,287 --> 00:15:55,513
然后就离开
and then he leaves it.

281
00:15:55,550 --> 00:15:57,925
那么有人能在晚上出入那里吗?
So anyone can visit it during the night?

282
00:15:58,461 --> 00:16:00,212
我想是的
I suppose so.

283
00:16:00,248 --> 00:16:02,508
但伙计拿着大门的钥匙
But the lad has the key to the outer door.

284
00:16:02,546 --> 00:16:04,594
知道了
I see.

285
00:16:04,632 --> 00:16:07,908
你提到的那个旅店叫什么?
What is the name of that tavern you spoke of?

286
00:16:07,946 --> 00:16:09,310
Green Dragon
Green Dragon.

287
00:16:09,348 --> 00:16:12,649
在Parkshire有不错的钓鱼点吧?
Is there any good fishing in that part of Parkshire?

288
00:16:12,686 --> 00:16:15,460
河沟里有鲑鱼
There's trout in the millstream

289
00:16:15,498 --> 00:16:17,481
湖里有梭子鱼
and pike in the lake.

290
00:16:17,518 --> 00:16:18,077
已经够好了
That's good enough.

291
00:16:18,114 --> 00:16:19,962
你认为这是什么 华生?
What do you make of it, Watson?

292
00:16:19,999 --> 00:16:23,470
这是大腿的上髁
It's the upper contour of a femur.

293
00:16:33,275 --> 00:16:34,584
人骨吗?
Human?

294
00:16:35,163 --> 00:16:37,257
毫无疑问
Without a doubt.

295
00:16:44,403 --> 00:16:47,634
这是在唬人 先生
It's a bluff, sir.

296
00:16:48,663 --> 00:16:50,202
可能是任何人寄来的
Anyone could have sent it.

297
00:16:50,239 --> 00:16:52,182
也许是个马探子
It could be a tout.

298
00:16:52,220 --> 00:16:53,810
我不在乎谁写的
I don't care who it is.

299
00:16:53,847 --> 00:16:56,712
我要知道他所写的内容中 是否有属实的部分
I need to know if there's any truth in what he's written.

300
00:16:58,814 --> 00:17:01,687
我离开的期间 Carrie负责照顾家中事务
Carrie will be in charge of the house while I'm away.

301
00:17:02,685 --> 00:17:04,394
Carrie吗 先生?
Carrie, sir?

302
00:17:04,431 --> 00:17:06,923
你得把心思放在"王子"的训练上
Your concern must be for the Prince's training.

303
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:10,997
没有再比那更重要的事了
Nothing is more important than that.

304
00:17:11,713 --> 00:17:13,757
53...
Fifty-three,

305
00:17:13,795 --> 00:17:15,718
54...
Fifty-four,

306
00:17:15,755 --> 00:17:18,412
55...
Fifty-five.

307
00:17:19,290 --> 00:17:20,444
有何吩咐 女士?
Yes, ma'am?

308
00:17:20,481 --> 00:17:23,891
谢谢 Stephens 把餐盘拿走吧
Thank you, Stephens, please take the tray now.

309
00:17:26,756 --> 00:17:28,567
56...
Fifty-six.

310
00:17:33,925 --> 00:17:35,816
我黎明时出发
I leave at dawn.

311
00:18:48,398 --> 00:18:49,838
两间房是吗 先生?
Two room,is that right, sir?

312
00:18:49,876 --> 00:18:50,932
再要两杯你这儿最好的酒
And two glasses of your best ale.

313
00:18:50,969 --> 00:18:52,012
好的 先生
Right, sir.

314
00:18:55,368 --> 00:18:56,766
-福尔摩斯 -嗯?
Holmes? Hm?

315
00:18:57,336 --> 00:18:58,333
嘘
Sh.

316
00:18:59,525 --> 00:19:01,637
先生们 你们好
Good day, gentlemen?

317
00:19:01,675 --> 00:19:03,547
你好 老家伙
Hello, old fellow.

318
00:19:03,584 --> 00:19:04,614
哦 女士们 不好意思
Oh, ladies, I'm so sorry.

319
00:19:04,652 --> 00:19:06,347
我刚才没注意你们坐在这
I didn't see you sitting there.

320
00:19:07,974 --> 00:19:10,605
这里真是寒风凛冽啊 不是吗?
There's quite a bite in the air, isn't there?

321
00:19:10,644 --> 00:19:13,109
你想要更自由些吧?
Oh, you'd much rather be free, wouldn't you?

322
00:19:15,431 --> 00:19:16,551
老板!
Landlord!

323
00:19:16,589 --> 00:19:20,057
难道一定要把这条狗栓得这么紧吗?
Is it really necessary to keep this dog tied up like this?

324
00:19:20,095 --> 00:19:20,768
先生 如果不栓紧了
If I didn't, sir,

325
00:19:20,805 --> 00:19:22,422
它一溜烟就会跑回原来的主人家
it'd be off back to the owner in a jiffy.

326
00:19:22,459 --> 00:19:25,024
你看 先生 Jasper是只Shoscombe犬
You see, sir, Jasper's a Shoscombe spaniel.

327
00:19:25,062 --> 00:19:26,218
哦 我本该看出来的
Oh, I should have known.

328
00:19:26,255 --> 00:19:29,262
瞧 我也是个爱狗之人
You see, I'm quite a dog enthusiast myself.

329
00:19:30,183 --> 00:19:31,191
等等
Wait.

330
00:19:31,229 --> 00:19:32,645
拿行李时小心点
Be careful with that luggage

331
00:19:32,682 --> 00:19:34,621
否则我活剥了你的皮
or I'll skin you alive.

332
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:39,600
请别放心里去 先生们
Don't you mind him, sirs.

333
00:19:39,639 --> 00:19:42,130
他还要照顾他的母亲
He takes after his mother.

334
00:19:45,661 --> 00:19:47,370
是出来钓鱼的吗?
Out for a bit of fishing, hey?

335
00:19:47,408 --> 00:19:49,416
我们想在Hole湖
We thought we might try and land a pike or two

336
00:19:49,452 --> 00:19:50,215
钓几条梭子鱼
at the Hole Lake.

337
00:19:50,253 --> 00:19:52,148
没等你钓到鱼
You might find yourselves in the lake

338
00:19:52,185 --> 00:19:53,760
你自己就先掉里头去了
before you were through.

339
00:19:56,817 --> 00:19:57,849
为什么呢?
Why is that?

340
00:19:57,887 --> 00:20:00,027
因为Robert爵士极度警惕
That Sir Robert is terrible jealous of anyone

341
00:20:00,064 --> 00:20:02,104
怕有人监视他的马厩
who might be spying on his stables.

342
00:20:02,142 --> 00:20:03,799
我们又不是马探子
Well, we're not touts.

343
00:20:03,836 --> 00:20:08,507
他是那种先斩后奏的人
He's the sort that strikes first and speaks afterwards.

344
00:20:10,621 --> 00:20:12,786
华生 我们午餐前
Watson, I think we should take a little walk

345
00:20:12,824 --> 00:20:14,005
出去走走吧
before lunch.

346
00:20:14,798 --> 00:20:18,146
主意不错
Well, that's a splendid idea.

347
00:20:19,374 --> 00:20:21,893
老板 我们可以把狗带上吗?
Do you think we could take the dog with us, Landlord?

348
00:20:21,931 --> 00:20:23,270
当然可以 先生们
By all means, gentlemen.

349
00:20:23,307 --> 00:20:26,812
只是记得我说的关于Robert爵士的事
But mind what I said about Sir Robert.

350
00:20:31,792 --> 00:20:34,665
走这边 华生
It's this way, Watson.

351
00:20:54,375 --> 00:20:55,652
Robert爵士现在如何了?
What about Sir Robert?

352
00:20:55,984 --> 00:20:56,942
据我估计
By my estimate,

353
00:20:56,979 --> 00:20:59,074
他现在应该在去York的路上
he should be well on his way to York by now.

354
00:20:59,112 --> 00:20:59,917
你怎么知道的?
How do you know that?

355
00:20:59,954 --> 00:21:01,937
因为我给他发了封电报
Because I had a telegram sent to him.

356
00:21:01,973 --> 00:21:04,743
福尔摩斯 你有什么目的?
Holmes, what have you been up to?

357
00:21:04,782 --> 00:21:06,481
当然 Palmer是最有希望获胜的
Of course, Palmer's the Favorite

358
00:21:06,518 --> 00:21:08,091
就养在York附近的马厩里
is stabled somewhere near York.

359
00:21:08,128 --> 00:21:10,351
我只是提示他那匹马
I merely advised him that the horse has shown

360
00:21:10,389 --> 00:21:11,763
最近几天有了长足的进步
much improvement in the last few days.

361
00:21:11,801 --> 00:21:14,011
当他发现自己被愚弄了可不会高兴的
He won't be pleased when he finds he's been duped.

362
00:21:14,049 --> 00:21:15,756
我确定他会气急败坏
I'm sure he'll be furious.

363
