00:23:08,002 --> 00:23:09,228
Jasper
Jasper.

402
00:23:12,372 --> 00:23:13,361
来啊 孩子
Come on, boy.

403
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:15,984
来啊 我可不是在玩
Come on. I'm not playing games now.

404
00:23:35,201 --> 00:23:36,666
Jasper
Jasper.

405
00:24:16,469 --> 00:24:19,397
这里离庄园有多远?
How far are we away from the hall?

406
00:24:19,435 --> 00:24:22,068
大约四分之一英里 先生
About a quarter of a mile, sir.

407
00:24:22,106 --> 00:24:27,068
Beatrice夫人是在正午乘车出行吧?
I'm correct in thinking that  Lady Beatrice takes a drive about midday?

408
00:24:27,105 --> 00:24:27,627
对 先生
Yes, sir.

409
00:24:27,664 --> 00:24:29,415
谢谢 事不宜迟
Thank you, we've not a moment to lose.

410
00:24:29,453 --> 00:24:31,354
快走 Jasper 快走 华生 快走
Come Jasper, come Watson, come.

411
00:25:15,803 --> 00:25:16,944
拦住马车 华生
Stop the carriage, Watson,

412
00:25:16,981 --> 00:25:18,680
拦住马车
stop the carriage!

413
00:25:24,025 --> 00:25:25,108
不好意思
Excuse me.

414
00:25:30,221 --> 00:25:33,921
请问去镇上的Green Dragon该怎么走?
Could you direct us to the Green Dragon in town?

415
00:25:38,447 --> 00:25:41,213
快走 快走
Drive on, drive on.

416
00:25:43,421 --> 00:25:45,123
呆着 别过来
Stay, stay back.

417
00:25:45,934 --> 00:25:47,749
别过来
Stay back.

418
00:26:02,988 --> 00:26:04,191
在Beatrice夫人明天再次乘车出行之前
Well, there's nothing we can do

419
00:26:04,229 --> 00:26:07,225
我们没什么能做的
until Lady Beatrice takes her drive again tomorrow.

420
00:26:07,775 --> 00:26:08,712
你还没解释为什么
You still haven't explained

421
00:26:08,749 --> 00:26:10,512
今天午后要我那样冒险拦车
why I risked my life this afternoon.

422
00:26:10,550 --> 00:26:12,341
为了验证一个推理
To test a theory.

423
00:26:12,378 --> 00:26:13,177
你一定很失望
You must be very disappointed.

424
00:26:13,214 --> 00:26:14,645
没验证成功却害我差点丧命
I was almost killed instead.

425
00:26:14,681 --> 00:26:17,706
相反 我想我的小实验很成功
On the contrary, I think my little experiment was quite successful.

426
00:26:17,744 --> 00:26:18,892
我怎么没看出来
I fail to see how.

427
00:26:19,632 --> 00:26:23,517
那只狗 华生 狗
The dog, Watson, the dog.

428
00:26:23,554 --> 00:26:26,964
没想到什么吗?
Did that suggest nothing to you?

429
00:26:27,002 --> 00:26:28,858
Carrie Evans决意
Well, Carrie Evans is determined

430
00:26:28,895 --> 00:26:31,369
要让狗和女主人不能相见
to keep the dog and her mistress apart so.

431
00:26:31,407 --> 00:26:32,461
没有别的吗?
There is an alternative?

432
00:26:32,498 --> 00:26:33,646
有啊
Yes,

433
00:26:33,683 --> 00:26:34,911
Robert爵士把那个放债人
that Sir Robert has done away with

434
00:26:34,949 --> 00:26:36,530
Samuel Brewer做掉了
the moneylender, Samuel Brewer.

435
00:26:36,567 --> 00:26:38,876
别忘了
Don't forget.

436
00:26:38,914 --> 00:26:41,451
别忘了发现的人骨
Don't forget the human bone that was found.

437
00:26:41,490 --> 00:26:42,612
我没忘
I haven't forgotten.

438
00:26:42,649 --> 00:26:44,402
对我来讲 显而易见
It's perfectly clear to me.

439
00:26:44,439 --> 00:26:46,355
他们之前有过争执
They've crossed swords before.

440
00:26:46,392 --> 00:26:47,897
很可能这次Robert爵士
It's possible that Sir Robert

441
00:26:47,934 --> 00:26:49,063
做得太过分了
has gone too far this time,

442
00:26:49,101 --> 00:26:50,224
犯了谋杀罪
and is guilty of murder.

443
00:26:52,596 --> 00:26:53,871
那个孩子发现的
What the boy found

444
00:26:53,909 --> 00:26:56,984
正是那位不幸的放债人的遗体
is all that remains of the unfortunate moneylender.

445
00:26:57,022 --> 00:26:58,119
哦 不 不 谢谢你
Oh, no, no, thank you.

446
00:26:58,156 --> 00:26:59,329
我饿死了
I'm famished.

447
00:27:01,599 --> 00:27:03,935
新抓到的 福尔摩斯先生
A fresh catch, Mr. Holmes?

448
00:27:05,077 --> 00:27:08,521
好久都没见到这么棒的了
Best I've seen in a long time.

449
00:27:11,764 --> 00:27:14,999
真是"水深火热"啊 华生
These are deep waters, Watson.

450
00:27:15,038 --> 00:27:19,041
水深火热 浊而不清
Deep and rather dirty.

451
00:27:22,045 --> 00:27:24,759
我想借用地下室的钥匙
I would like to borrow the key to the cellar.

452
00:27:24,797 --> 00:27:26,037
干什么用 福尔摩斯先生?
For what purpose, Mr. Holmes?

453
00:27:26,074 --> 00:27:27,648
为了进门
To get inside.

454
00:27:28,631 --> 00:27:29,867
Robert爵士在哪儿?
Where is Sir Robert?

455
00:27:29,903 --> 00:27:31,751
Robert爵士昨天一早
Well, Sir Robert left for York

456
00:27:31,789 --> 00:27:33,290
去York了
early yesterday morning.

457
00:27:33,327 --> 00:27:36,045
今晚才能回来
He isn't expected back till some time tonight.

458
00:27:36,083 --> 00:27:39,059
我本应带你四处看看
I'd show you around the house myself,

459
00:27:39,096 --> 00:27:41,796
但主人走了 Carrie负责
but master left Carrie in charge,

460
00:27:41,833 --> 00:27:43,427
她不会让任何人跨入大门一步的
and she won't let anyone past the door.

461
00:27:43,466 --> 00:27:45,952
他指派一个女仆掌管庄园?
He left a maid in charge of the house?

462
00:27:45,989 --> 00:27:50,013
我告诉过您 主人和夫人有过节
I told you things were bad between master and her ladyship.

463
00:27:50,051 --> 00:27:53,237
Beatrice夫人的房间在哪儿?
Whereabouts is Lady Beatrice's room?

464
00:27:53,274 --> 00:27:54,450
在一层 福尔摩斯先生
It's on the ground floor, Mr. Holmes,

465
00:27:54,489 --> 00:27:56,040
因为她的心脏不好
on account of her ladyship's heart.

466
00:27:56,076 --> 00:27:58,574
刚好在底层的...?
Precisely on the ground floor where?

467
00:27:58,612 --> 00:28:01,122
走廊里第二间房
Second room in the corridor beside

468
00:28:01,159 --> 00:28:03,234
在地下室入口旁边
the cellar passageway.

469
00:28:03,273 --> 00:28:05,215
自从我们在Baker街的谈话之后
Has there been any change in the running of the house

470
00:28:05,253 --> 00:28:07,237
房子里的人事有什么变化吗
since we spoke at Baker Street?

471
00:28:07,273 --> 00:28:10,873
没想到有什么 除了我得解雇Harvey
None that I can think of, apart from the fact that

472
00:28:10,912 --> 00:28:13,036
我的一个伙计
I had to dismiss Harvey, one of my stable lads.

473
00:28:13,074 --> 00:28:15,633
他就那个在炉子里发现骨头的人?
Wasn't he the one that found the bone in the furnace?

474
00:28:15,670 --> 00:28:16,385
是的
That's right.

475
00:28:16,422 --> 00:28:19,112
为什么要解雇他?
What is the reason for his dismissal?

476
00:28:19,150 --> 00:28:21,315
他偷了这里某个
Well, he'd stolen some money

477
00:28:21,353 --> 00:28:24,019
雇员的钱 所以...
from somebody on the staff and so.

478
00:28:24,056 --> 00:28:27,430
啊 这就是"王子" 福尔摩斯先生
Ah, here's the Prince himself, Mr. Holmes.

479
00:28:32,823 --> 00:28:34,725
全身都闪耀着冠军的光芒 你说呢?
Every inch a champion, wouldn't you say?

480
00:28:34,763 --> 00:28:36,736
是啊 非常出色的生灵
Yes, he's a very fine creature,

481
00:28:36,774 --> 00:28:39,681
但你才是专家 华生
but you're the expert, Watson.

482
00:28:39,719 --> 00:28:41,140
根本不是什么专家 福尔摩斯
Hardly an expert, Holmes.

483
00:28:41,177 --> 00:28:43,399
我刚刚看到"王子"在
I am aware of the Prince's bursts of speed

484
00:28:43,437 --> 00:28:46,637
最后一弗隆(英国长度单位)的爆发力 但问题是
over a final furlong but the fact is

485
00:28:46,674 --> 00:28:48,483
它没有在大赛上赢过
he hasn't yet won a major race.

486
00:28:48,521 --> 00:28:50,828
你是否依然认为它有很大胜算?
Do you think he's still in with a good chance?

487
00:28:50,865 --> 00:28:53,867
如果它已经充分准备 那么是的
If he's given the ground, then yes.

488
00:29:30,506 --> 00:29:32,800
好吧 好吧 等一下
All right, all right, hold your horses.

489
00:29:32,839 --> 00:29:35,060
我来了 我来了
I'm coming, I'm coming.

490
00:29:36,963 --> 00:29:38,771
下午好
Good afternoon.

491
00:29:38,808 --> 00:29:41,335
你一定是Stephens
You must be Stephens.

492
00:29:42,246 --> 00:29:43,223
是的 先生
That's right, sir.

493
00:29:43,259 --> 00:29:45,099
我是位医生
I'm a doctor.

494
00:29:45,137 --> 00:29:47,512
Robert爵士让我一有时间
Well, Sir Robert asked me to call on his sister

495
00:29:47,549 --> 00:29:48,457
就来拜访他的姐姐
at the first opportunity.

496
00:29:48,495 --> 00:29:49,409
我刚到此地
I'm new to the area.

497
00:29:49,446 --> 00:29:51,515
他没跟我说过 先生
Well, he said nothing about it to me, sir.

498
00:29:51,552 --> 00:29:52,925
他肯定是忘了
Well, he must have forgotten.

499
00:29:52,964 --> 00:29:55,873
对于Robert爵士这样的大忙人来说一点不奇怪
Hardly surprising for a man as busy as Sir Robert.

500
00:29:55,910 --> 00:29:58,349
恐怕夫人现在
I'm afraid her ladyship is out

501
00:29:58,387 --> 00:30:00,648
在外面乘车兜风呢
taking her carriage exercise at the moment.

502
00:30:00,686 --> 00:30:03,051
多长时间能回来呢?
How long is she likely to be?

503
00:30:03,088 --> 00:30:05,479
不超过半小时 先生
Well, no more than half an hour, sir.

504
00:30:05,518 --> 00:30:09,182
那这样的话 我不介意等着
Well, in that case I don't mind waiting.

505
00:30:13,431 --> 00:30:16,156
看起来你也有病痛
You appear to be in some pain yourself.

506
00:30:16,194 --> 00:30:19,819
是风湿病 先生
Well, it's the rheumatics, sir.

507
00:30:19,858 --> 00:30:21,689
这把老骨头曾经
These old bones have taken a pounding

508
00:30:21,726 --> 00:30:22,553
受过伤
in their time.

509
00:30:22,590 --> 00:30:24,372
健康状况大不如前啦
Health's not what it was.

510
00:30:24,410 --> 00:30:26,569
为什么不跟我说说呢?
Now, why don't you tell me about it?

511
00:30:26,607 --> 00:30:28,073
您的意思是?
Beg pardon, sir?

512
00:30:28,110 --> 00:30:29,007
既然我在这儿
Well, now that I'm here,

513
00:30:29,043 --> 00:30:31,251
那不如看看我能帮上什么忙
I might as well make myself useful.

514
00:30:31,289 --> 00:30:33,722
哦 你人真好 先生
Oh, that's very kind of you, sir.

515
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:34,370
谢谢
Thank you.

516
00:30:34,407 --> 00:30:38,516
是从我的手腕末端开始的
Well, it starts in the bottom of my wrist.

517
00:30:38,553 --> 00:30:40,243
然后逐渐向上
And then it goes up.

518
00:30:40,281 --> 00:30:42,085
到肩膀?
In your shoulder?

519
00:31:46,423 --> 00:31:50,077
"S.B."
S.B.

520
00:32:02,972 --> 00:32:04,959
当然 早晨一起床时
Of course, the worst time is

521
00:32:04,996 --> 00:32:07,018
最难熬
first thing in the morning.

522
00:32:07,056 --> 00:32:09,138
我的脖子和胳膊
My back and my legs,

523
00:32:09,176 --> 00:32:12,125
哦 跟木板一样僵硬
oh, stiff as a board.

524
00:32:14,393 --> 00:32:15,608
还有我的脚
And my feet,

525
00:32:15,644 --> 00:32:18,553
我跟你说过我的脚吗?
did I tell you about my feet?

526
00:32:19,230 --> 00:32:20,331
没有
No.

527
00:32:20,368 --> 00:32:22,578
哦 我得跟你说说我的脚
Oh, I'll tell you about my feet.

528
00:32:22,616 --> 00:32:25,304
冰块 就像冰块
Blocks of ice, like blocks of ice.

529
00:32:25,341 --> 00:32:27,015
有时我都感觉不到脚的存在
Can't feel them sometimes.

530
00:32:27,052 --> 00:32:30,110
你的血液循环不顺畅
Your blood's not circulating properly.

531
00:32:30,148 --> 00:32:31,017
是个常见问题
It's a common problem.

532
00:32:31,054 --> 00:32:36,779
还有另外一个问题
And then there's the other trouble.

533
00:32:39,854 --> 00:32:41,457
另外一个问题?
The other trouble?

534
00:32:42,713 --> 00:32:45,987
你知道的 另外一个问题
You know, the other trouble.

535
00:34:04,412 --> 00:34:05,744
我试过各种方法
I've tried everything,

536
00:34:05,781 --> 00:34:08,630
但都根本没什么起色
but it doesn't make any difference at all.

537
00:34:08,668 --> 00:34:11,775
和以前一样痛苦
I'm in just as much agony now as I ever was.

538
00:34:28,145 --> 00:34:30,598
袖子卷起来吧
Roll it right up.

539
00:34:31,801 --> 00:34:33,637
哦 那是夫人
Oh, that'll be her ladyship.

540
00:34:33,675 --> 00:34:36,542
她回来早了
She's back early.

541
00:34:37,128 --> 00:34:38,544
很抱歉 不过恐怕
Please excuse me, but I'm afraid

542
00:34:38,582 --> 00:34:42,073
我还有另一个紧急的门诊
I have another urgent appointment.

543
00:35:12,970 --> 00:35:14,512
快到了 夫人
Almost there, my lady.

544
00:35:14,550 --> 00:35:18,789
谢谢 Stephens 这就可以了
Thank you, Stephens, we'll be all right now.

545
00:35:18,825 --> 00:35:22,018
谢谢 Stephens
Thank you, Stephens.

546
00:35:23,113 --> 00:35:25,332
好吧 小姐
Right you are, Miss.

547
00:35:43,799 --> 00:35:46,585
奇怪
Strange.

548
00:35:56,094 --> 00:35:57,787
福尔摩斯 谢天谢地
Holmes, thank goodness.

549
00:35:57,825 --> 00:35:59,741
幸亏卧室在底层
Fortunately, the bedroom is on the ground floor.

550
00:35:59,778 --> 00:36:00,967
有什么新发现吗?
Did you have any luck?

551
00:36:01,003 --> 00:36:02,735
一些事情还不明朗
A few things are still unclear,

552
00:36:02,773 --> 00:36:03,621
但我希望
but before the night is out,

553
00:36:03,658 --> 00:36:05,323
在天明之前解决
I hope to have solved the mystery

554
00:36:05,361 --> 00:36:07,533
Shoscombe别墅的谜题
of Shoscombe Old Place.

555
00:36:23,683 --> 00:36:26,985
假设Samuel Brewer再来庄园要钱
If Samuel Brewer returned to the hall to demand his money,

556
00:36:27,023 --> 00:36:28,483
他可能会在晚上来
he might have done so at night.

557
00:36:28,521 --> 00:36:30,211
可能就是Robert爵士
He could have been the man

558
00:36:30,248 --> 00:36:33,756
在老教堂所见的人
that Sir Robert met at the old church.

559
00:36:35,054 --> 00:36:37,871
可能Robert爵士大发雷霆
Perhaps Sir Robert flew into one of his rages

560
00:36:37,909 --> 00:36:39,293
并杀了他
and killed him,

561
00:36:40,073 --> 00:36:42,218
在惊慌失措中
and in a moment of sheer panic

562
00:36:42,256 --> 00:36:44,084
把他丢进炉子
tried to dispose of the body

563
00:36:44,122 --> 00:36:45,888
以处理尸体
by putting it into the furnace.

564
00:36:45,924 --> 00:36:48,949
因此 这个钱包(出现在了那里)
Hence, the note case.

565
00:36:48,987 --> 00:36:51,798
华生 别动!
Watson, the vibrations!

566
00:36:53,776 --> 00:36:55,030
或许我得承认
If perhaps maybe I admit

567
00:36:55,068 --> 00:36:57,748
我们现在掌握的都是间接证据
all the evidence we have so far is purely circumstantial.

568
00:37:00,279 --> 00:37:01,035
哦
Oh.

569
00:37:27,602 --> 00:37:29,266
松香
Resin.

570
00:37:30,119 --> 00:37:31,178
松香?
Resin?

571
00:37:37,777 --> 00:37:40,192
含有酒精成分
On an alcohol base.

572
00:37:42,103 --> 00:37:45,618
这是在Beatrice夫人的房间里
Traces of it on a few strands of hair

573
00:37:45,656 --> 00:37:48,431
找到的几根头发
found in Lady Beatrice's room.

574
00:37:50,946 --> 00:37:52,064
来 华生
Come, Watson.

575
00:37:52,102 --> 00:37:53,016
电报可不会让
The telegram will not

576
00:37:53,054 --> 00:37:55,039
Robert在那儿呆很久
keep Sir Robert away much longer.

577
00:37:55,075 --> 00:37:56,853
我们要去哪儿?
Where are we going?

578
00:38:12,881 --> 00:38:13,802
Robert爵士
Sir Robert.

579
00:38:20,471 --> 00:38:22,936
我不在的时候发生了什么事?
What happened while I was away?

580
00:38:23,801 --> 00:38:24,488
没什么事 先生
Nothing, sir.

581
00:38:24,525 --> 00:38:25,956
别骗我 Mason
Don't lie to me, Mason.

582
00:38:25,992 --> 00:38:30,093
有人在背着我干一些事
Something's been going on behind my back.

583
00:38:33,173 --> 00:38:35,342
是不是有人在这附近盘问?
Has anyone been around here asking questions?

584
00:38:35,380 --> 00:38:37,470
没有人 先生
No one, sir.

585
00:38:39,607 --> 00:38:43,201
但我在Crendall附近遇到一些人
Apart from some people I met near Crendall.

586
00:38:45,751 --> 00:38:47,477
我不知道他们的名字
I don't know their names.

587
00:38:47,514 --> 00:38:49,346
你们说了些什么?
What did you talk about?

588
00:38:49,384 --> 00:38:51,299
没什么
Nothing much.

589
00:38:51,336 --> 00:38:54,285
他们对老教堂很感兴趣
They were interested in the old church.

590
00:38:56,198 --> 00:38:57,724
笨蛋!
Fool!

591
00:39:06,547 --> 00:39:09,650
如果Samuel Brewer不是受害者
Well, if Samuel Brewer was not the victim,

592
00:39:09,688 --> 00:39:11,593
那为什么他的钱包
why was his note case found

593
00:39:11,594 --> 00:39:13,239
会在庄园的地下室里找到呢?
in the cellar of the hall?

594
00:39:13,276 --> 00:39:16,525
这里还有谁的名字是以S.B.开头的?
Who else in the household has the initials S. B?

595
00:39:16,563 --> 00:39:19,429
S.B.... S.B.
S.B., S.B.

596
00:39:19,466 --> 00:39:21,716
Sandy Bain
Sandy Bain.

597
00:39:21,754 --> 00:39:24,988
Harvey因为偷了别人的钱
Harvey was dismissed

598
00:39:25,026 --> 00:39:28,090
而被逐出了房子
for stealing from other members of the household.

599
00:39:28,848 --> 00:39:29,807
他的职责之一
One of his duties

600
00:39:29,844 --> 00:39:32,060
就是照看地下室的炉子
was to tend to the furnace in the cellar.

601
00:39:32,098 --> 00:39:34,455
事实上的确有尸体被烧了
Well, the fact remains that the body was burned.

602
00:39:34,492 --> 00:39:36,898
如果那不是Brewer
If it wasn't Brewer's,

603
00:39:36,936 --> 00:39:38,551
又会是谁?
then whose was it?

604
00:40:16,638 --> 00:40:18,446
福尔摩斯
Holmes.

605
00:41:15,778 --> 00:41:17,330
在这样一个地方
What could you possibly be able to find

606
00:41:17,366 --> 00:41:19,576
能找到什么呢?
in a place like this?

607
00:41:22,044 --> 00:41:24,988
铅衬被切掉了
The lead lining's been cut.

608
00:41:37,009 --> 00:41:38,647
不出我所料
Just as I thought.

609
00:41:39,430 --> 00:41:41,743
螺钉松了
The bolts have been loosened.

610
00:41:45,205 --> 00:41:49,401
华生 我需要你帮忙把这个打开
Watson, I'm going to need your help to open this.

611
00:41:49,438 --> 00:41:51,695
福尔摩斯 这是亵渎神明啊
Holmes, that's desecration.

612
00:42:19,641 --> 00:42:20,779
你是谁?
Who are you?

613
00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:23,932
你动我的东西干什么?
What are you doing on my property?

614
00:42:23,971 --> 00:42:25,508
听见没有?
Do you hear?

615
00:42:25,545 --> 00:42:26,216
你是谁?
Who are you?

616
00:42:26,567 --> 00:42:28,705
你在这儿干什么?
What are you doing here?

617
00:42:33,074 --> 00:42:34,980
哦
Oh.

618
00:43:04,582 --> 00:43:06,465
啊 福尔摩斯先生
Ah, Mr. Holmes,

619
00:43:06,502 --> 00:43:08,151
发生了什么事?
what's happened?

620
00:43:08,189 --> 00:43:09,128
问得好 Mason先生
A good question, Mr. Mason.

621
00:43:09,165 --> 00:43:11,791
问题直指Robert爵士
One that should be directed at Sir Robert.

622
00:43:12,951 --> 00:43:16,164
啊 该死的装置
Oh, blasted contraptions.

623
00:43:18,237 --> 00:43:19,919
你怎么敢? 出去
How dare you? Get out.

624
00:43:19,957 --> 00:43:21,903
我本想跟你们一起喝茶的
I was going to join you for tea,

625
00:43:21,940 --> 00:43:23,948
但我好像来晚了
but I see I'm too late.

626
00:43:23,986 --> 00:43:26,737
马上出去 否则我就叫Robert爵士了
Get out this instant or I'll call for Sir Robert.

627
00:43:26,774 --> 00:43:28,035
Robert爵士知道我在这儿
Sir Robert knows that I'm here.

628
00:43:28,073 --> 00:43:30,965
Evans小姐 请坐下好吗?
Please, Miss Evans, will you sit down?

629
00:43:33,835 --> 00:43:36,153
我想如果不来向Beatrice致敬
I felt I couldn't visit Shoscombe Old Place

630
00:43:36,192 --> 00:43:38,632
我就不能拜访Shoscombe别墅
without paying my respects to Lady Beatrice.

631
00:43:41,119 --> 00:43:44,156
哦 你们喝茶的时候还喝白兰地
Oh, you have brandy with your tea?

632
00:43:45,533 --> 00:43:50,148
当然是用来治疗的
For medicinal purposes, of course.

633
00:43:51,435 --> 00:43:53,496
但这是不是足以让我好奇?
But is it enough I wonder?

634
00:43:53,533 --> 00:43:55,009
好奇什么?
Enough for what?

635
00:43:55,046 --> 00:43:58,415
白兰地是用来恢复精神的
Brandy revives the spirits.

636
00:43:58,453 --> 00:44:00,444
我不认为这足够
I hardly think it is sufficient

637
00:44:00,481 --> 00:44:02,989
用来唤醒死人
to raise the dead.

638
00:44:03,027 --> 00:44:07,866
别动 Evans小姐
Don't move, Miss. Evans.

639
00:44:51,260 --> 00:44:53,812
这样你就好受多了
That should be comfortable enough

640
00:44:53,849 --> 00:44:55,569
等你自己的医生来吧
until your own doctor arrives.

641
00:44:55,607 --> 00:44:57,065
谢谢
Thank you.

642
00:44:57,102 --> 00:44:58,670
我是夏洛克 福尔摩斯
I am Sherlock Holmes.

643
00:44:58,708 --> 00:45:00,891
或许你对我的名字很熟悉
Perhaps my name is familiar to you.

644
00:45:00,928 --> 00:45:04,788
或许表面看来并非如此
I know appearances are against me,

645
00:45:04,825 --> 00:45:06,382
但你必须相信
but you must believe that

646
00:45:06,420 --> 00:45:07,834
我别无选择
I could act in no other way.

647
00:45:07,871 --> 00:45:10,695
我很高兴你这样说
I'm very happy to hear you say so.

648
00:45:10,733 --> 00:45:12,072
但我恐怕你得跟
But I fear your explanations

649
00:45:12,109 --> 00:45:14,182
警察解释这些了
must be for the police.

650
00:45:14,220 --> 00:45:16,887
求你了 Robert爵士
Please, Sir Robert.

651
00:45:16,924 --> 00:45:19,900
这些行为的一切责任都由我一人承担
The responsibility for what has  been done is entirely mine.

652
00:45:20,485 --> 00:45:22,216
Evans小姐和Joe Barnes
Ms. Evans and Joe Barnes

653
00:45:22,254 --> 00:45:24,460
只是听从我的指示
were merely following my instructions.

654
00:45:24,497 --> 00:45:25,986
你必须保证他们不受伤害
You must promise that they will come to no harm.

655
00:45:26,024 --> 00:45:28,108
我无法跟你保证任何事
I can promise you nothing.

656
00:45:29,611 --> 00:45:33,458
但我愿意听一听事情的真相
But I will hear a plain statement of the facts.

657
00:45:33,494 --> 00:45:34,971
很好
Very well.

658
00:45:35,683 --> 00:45:37,201
显然你对我的事情
You've clearly gone pretty deeply

659
00:45:37,239 --> 00:45:38,313
已经了如指掌
into my affairs,

660
00:45:38,350 --> 00:45:41,048
否则我不会在那儿碰到你
otherwise I should not have found you where I did.

661
00:45:41,902 --> 00:45:45,902
我始终清楚如果Beatrice去世
I've always known that if Beatrice died,

662
00:45:45,939 --> 00:45:47,654
地产将归由
the estate would revert

663
00:45:47,691 --> 00:45:49,768
我姐夫的家人所有
to my brother-in-law's family.

664
00:45:49,807 --> 00:45:50,922
所有东西都会被查封
Everything would be seized,

665
00:45:50,958 --> 00:45:55,331
包括我的马厩和马匹
including the stables and the horses.

666
00:45:57,027 --> 00:45:58,369
福尔摩斯先生
Well, Mr. Holmes,

667
00:45:58,406 --> 00:45:59,750
我姐姐一周前
my sister did die,

668
00:45:59,788 --> 00:46:01,904
的确去世了
just a week ago.

669
00:46:01,941 --> 00:46:03,004
而你没告诉任何人?
And you told no one?

670
00:46:03,042 --> 00:46:04,998
我没有多少选择余地
I had little alternative.

671
00:46:05,036 --> 00:46:07,987
如果我公之于众 我将面对全面的破产
If I told the truth, I faced absolute ruin.

672
00:46:08,025 --> 00:46:11,368
如果我延迟到比赛之后公开
But if I could stave things off until the race,

673
00:46:11,405 --> 00:46:13,665
我知道一切都会好转
I knew all might be well.

674
00:46:15,958 --> 00:46:17,418
Beatrice死于长期困扰她的
Beatrice died of the heart condition

675
00:46:17,455 --> 00:46:19,004
心脏问题
that had long afflicted her.

676
00:46:19,041 --> 00:46:22,163
这一点要由验尸官来确认
That will be for a coroner to decide.

677
00:46:22,200 --> 00:46:24,330
她的医生可以证明
Her own doctor would certify that for months,

678
00:46:24,367 --> 00:46:28,366
数月以来她的症状预示了这个结局
her symptoms had threatened such an end.

679
00:46:29,623 --> 00:46:33,224
Joe Barnes在Beatrice去世前一两天
Joe Barnes came to see me in search of work

680
00:46:33,262 --> 00:46:36,520
到我这里找工作
a day or two before Beatrice died.

681
00:46:36,558 --> 00:46:38,523
他看起来是个值得信赖的孩子
He seemed a trustworthy lad,

682
00:46:38,561 --> 00:46:41,496
所以我想到让他来
and it came into my mind that he might

683
00:46:41,534 --> 00:46:43,838
假扮我亲爱的姐姐
for a short time

684
00:46:43,875 --> 00:46:46,149
一段时间
impersonate my dear sister.

685
00:46:46,186 --> 00:46:48,877
只要"她"每天出现在马车上
It was but a case of appearing daily in her carriage

686
00:46:48,914 --> 00:46:51,406
因为没人会进她的房间
for no one need enter her room

687
00:46:51,444 --> 00:46:52,726
除了Evans小姐
save Miss. Evans.

688
00:46:52,762 --> 00:46:56,363
当然 我很信任她
Of course, I had to take her into my confidence.

689
00:46:57,530 --> 00:47:00,078
整个骗局让我也很痛苦
The whole deception distressed me greatly,

690
00:47:00,115 --> 00:47:03,006
但想不到其他办法
but I could see no other course to take.

691
00:47:03,649 --> 00:47:04,227
很自然
Naturally,

692
00:47:04,266 --> 00:47:06,570
尸体不能存放在卧室里
the body couldn't remain in the bedroom.

693
00:47:10,031 --> 00:47:11,227
第一天晚上
On the first night,

694
00:47:11,264 --> 00:47:12,829
Joe和我把尸体抬出来
Joe and I carried it out

695
00:47:12,867 --> 00:47:14,122
放到老磨坊里
to the old mill house.

696
00:47:14,160 --> 00:47:17,898
她的宠物狗跟着我们
We were followed by her pet spaniel

697
00:47:17,936 --> 00:47:21,380
并且之后它一直在门口狂吠
which afterwards howled continually at the door.

698
00:47:21,418 --> 00:47:25,260
所以我觉得应该找个更安全的地方
So I felt some safer place was needed.

699
00:47:28,796 --> 00:47:30,501
我赶走了狗
I got rid of the dog,

700
00:47:30,538 --> 00:47:32,187
我们把Beatrice
and we carried Beatrice

701
00:47:32,225 --> 00:47:34,132
抬到教堂的地下室
to the crypt of the church.

702
00:47:35,615 --> 00:47:37,941
我认为我们把她放在她丈夫的
It seemed to me to be no unworthy resting place

703
00:47:37,978 --> 00:47:40,331
一位先人的棺材中作为其安息之所
if we put her for a time in the coffin

704
00:47:40,368 --> 00:47:42,484
并没有什么不妥
of one of her husband's ancestors

705
00:47:43,288 --> 00:47:46,854
她仍身处神圣之地
lying in what is still consecrated ground.

706
00:47:47,596 --> 00:47:50,785
我每天都去向她致意
I paid my respects to her there every day.

707
00:48:45,424 --> 00:48:46,765
至于我们从棺材中
As to the old relics

708
00:48:46,802 --> 00:48:48,839
取出的遗体
which we took from the coffin,

709
00:48:48,877 --> 00:48:51,017
Joe和我把它移走了
Joe and I removed them.

710
00:48:51,055 --> 00:48:53,509
他晚上走出卧室并下楼
He descended from the bedroom at night

711
00:48:53,546 --> 00:48:56,732
在炉子里焚烧遗体
and burned them in the furnace.

712
00:49:01,003 --> 00:49:04,548
设计这么的复杂的诡计真的有必要吗?
Was it necessarily to lay that monstrous trap?

713
00:49:04,586 --> 00:49:06,094
我认为没人
I was determined that no one

714
00:49:06,131 --> 00:49:09,556
可以打扰我姐姐安息
should disturb my sister's rest.

715
00:49:09,594 --> 00:49:11,178
但你是怎么开始怀疑她的死的
But how you suspected her death

716
00:49:11,216 --> 00:49:12,689
我想不到
I cannot imagine.

717
00:49:12,727 --> 00:49:14,458
是这样 昨天
Well, yesterday,

718
00:49:14,496 --> 00:49:17,288
当Evans小姐命令马车夫开走时
when Miss. Evans ordered the carriage to drive on,

719
00:49:17,325 --> 00:49:20,077
我推断她是在害怕什么
I concluded that she was afraid of something.

720
00:49:20,115 --> 00:49:24,401
我怀疑她怕的正是Jasper
I suspected that something was Jasper.

721
00:49:25,394 --> 00:49:28,864
Evans小姐知道狗不会出错
Miss. Evans knew that dogs do not make mistakes.

722
00:49:28,901 --> 00:49:32,285
它会认出那不是它的女主人
He would have known that it wasn't his mistress.

723
00:49:32,324 --> 00:49:34,173
但我们必须把此事交由警察
But we must leave all this for the police.

724
00:49:34,211 --> 00:49:35,537
为什么?
But why?

725
00:49:35,574 --> 00:49:38,556
我只需要一两天
A day or two is all I need.

726
00:49:38,594 --> 00:49:40,418
求你保持沉默吧
Say nothing yet I beg of you.

727
00:49:40,456 --> 00:49:43,218
只要比赛开始
The race will have been run,

728
00:49:43,255 --> 00:49:46,102
我的噩梦就将结束
and my nightmare might be over.

729
00:49:47,908 --> 00:49:50,142
我全身心地爱着Beatrice
I loved Beatrice with all my heart,

730
00:49:51,138 --> 00:49:53,045
其中没有任何污辱或不敬
and there was no indignity or irreverence.

731
00:49:53,083 --> 00:49:56,432
我不觉得我污辱了死者
I don't feel I have wronged the dead.

732
00:49:56,612 --> 00:49:59,157
我知道我的动机很自私
I realize that my motives were selfish,

733
00:50:00,594 --> 00:50:01,993
但我姐姐是不会希望
but my sister would not have wished

734
00:50:02,030 --> 00:50:05,276
看到我破产的
to see me destroyed.

735
00:50:13,259 --> 00:50:16,337
但这并不意味着你有权违反法律
That does not entitle you to break the law.

736
00:50:27,108 --> 00:50:28,660
听听这个 福尔摩斯
Listen to this, Holmes.

737
00:50:29,422 --> 00:50:32,070
在"Shoscombe王子"昨日夺得
Following the success of Shoscombe Prince

738
00:50:32,108 --> 00:50:34,083
冠军锦标赛的冠军之后
in yesterday's Champion Stakes,

739
00:50:34,122 --> 00:50:38,226
Robert爵士得到了足够丰厚的奖金
Sir Robert has received sufficient winnings

740
00:50:38,263 --> 00:50:40,276
偿还了所有债务
to settle all his debts

741
00:50:40,313 --> 00:50:42,738
并足够他重新过上
with enough left to reestablish him

742
00:50:42,775 --> 00:50:44,674
优越的生活
in a fair position in life.

743
00:50:44,712 --> 00:50:45,499
啊
Ah.

744
00:50:47,111 --> 00:50:49,755
然而 Robert爵士姐姐的
However, the victory was marred

745
00:50:49,793 --> 00:50:51,538
突然去世
by the sudden death

746
00:50:51,574 --> 00:50:53,021
冲淡了胜利的喜悦
of Sir Robert's sister,

747
00:50:53,060 --> 00:50:55,159
Beatrice Folder夫人
Lady Beatrice Folder

748
00:50:55,196 --> 00:50:56,603
至少与他一样
whose love of horses

749
00:50:56,640 --> 00:50:59,473
热爱赛马
was at least as great as his own.

750
00:51:03,368 --> 00:51:05,484
甚至是避难在外的Samuel Brewer
Even the elusive Samuel Brewer

751
00:51:05,522 --> 00:51:08,336
也从其法国的避难所归来
has returned from his hideaway in France

752
00:51:08,374 --> 00:51:10,575
并发电报祝贺
to send a telegram of congratulations

753
00:51:10,611 --> 00:51:13,436
Robert爵士的胜利
to Sir Robert on his win.

754
00:51:13,475 --> 00:51:15,540
这表明债权人
It transpires that even creditors

755
00:51:15,577 --> 00:51:17,569
也还有自己的债权人啊
have their creditors.

756
00:51:17,606 --> 00:51:18,853
这解释了为什么Samuel Brewer
It explains why Samuel Brewer

757
00:51:18,891 --> 00:51:20,822
那么急于要回自己的钱财
was so anxious to get his money back.

758
00:51:20,860 --> 00:51:22,800
但发电报
But to send a telegram,

759
00:51:22,837 --> 00:51:26,580
真是赤裸裸的伪善
such a bare faced hypocrisy.

760
00:51:26,618 --> 00:51:29,542
那你靠"Shoscombe王子"赢了多少钱?
So how much did you win on Shoscombe Prince?

761
00:51:31,246 --> 00:51:32,424
20吉尼(英国旧金币)
Twenty guineas.

762
00:51:32,462 --> 00:51:34,997
真可耻
That's disgraceful.

763
00:51:38,394 --> 00:51:40,313
香槟 Hudson太太?
Champagne, Mrs. Hudson?

764
00:51:40,351 --> 00:51:43,825
当然了 正合时宜啊
Of course, in the circumstances.

765
00:51:43,863 --> 00:51:45,035
哦 你真好
Well, that's very good of you,

766
00:51:45,072 --> 00:51:46,828
但我只赢了20吉尼啊
but I've only won 20 guineas.

767
00:51:46,866 --> 00:51:49,124
再加上我的10吉尼
Plus my ten.

768
00:51:49,161 --> 00:51:51,685
你可不是唯一一个欲罢不能
You're not the only one that likes a plunge

769
00:51:51,723 --> 00:51:53,756
一次次去赌马的家伙 医生
on the horses from time to time, Doctor.

770
00:51:53,794 --> 00:51:56,997
哦 哈!
Oh, gee.

